    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 997-generation Carrera S is a superlative example of precision engineering. It features the 3.8L flat-six M97/01 power plant paired with a tactile 6-speed manual transaxle and a factory-optioned mechanical limited-slip differential. The chassis is bolstered by Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM) with a lowered ride height, ensuring neutral cornering and exceptional lateral grip. Meticulously maintained, the vehicle shows zero bore scoring, a clean DME report with no over-revs in ranges 3-6, and a perfectly preserved interior free of bolster wear or soft-touch delamination. Every bushing remains compliant, and the four-piston monoblock Brembo calipers provide immediate, fade-free deceleration. This is a turn-key, investment-grade machine for the discerning purist.",
